@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                          Editorial By Chris Seward
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

   Welcome back to AIO, last months issue was a bit hectic with all the
chaos of organizing the biggest and best issue of AIO ever and released
dates slipped etc so it all fell apart, but we managed to get the last
issue out even if it was 3 weeks late.. opps :( Due to all the things
going on last issue there was a mistake, the picture said that it was the
April issue where in the magazine itself it said it was the May issue,
due to AIO12 coming out so late it ended up being the May issue thus
skipping any April issue. So to clear it up there was no April issue.
 
   Well we are now here with the June issue which is on time, i've had
over a month to do this issue and it was a pleasant change giving me
plenty of time to do the issue and a bit of a break after 1 years solid
AIO production! It's back to its usual size again but with non of the
quality loss, still we are bringing you the latest reviews, news and
articles. This month we recieved Quake and Genetic species so look
out next month for full reviews of them both and them head-to-head to
see which comes out the better.

   Two sad losses this month, the first being the long running AIO utils
editor, Adrian Hendy, and the second being the newly employed Deputy
Editor, Paul Steadman. We now have both job places vacant and if you are
interested in being part of the fastest growing diskmag then please get
in touch with me the editor!

   With the summer rolling in AIO becomes harder to do with less time on
the computer because either it is to hot or i'm off sunning myself some
where, then there is always the World Cup which rules my life for a month
so i've been doing AIO at half times and any other spare time i can get.
Good luck to the England team!! Although all this has happend we have
survived a year and are planning to survive for many more years to come.

   No news breaking stories this month so the most exciting news is that
Genetic Species and Quake have both been released, until next month, ciao!

