Joe Torre, Senior Hardware Engineer

Joe Torre has been an in-the-trenches Amiga crusader since month-one, 1985.
As a hands-on hardware engineer, Joe still insists on building his
prototypes himself, rather than handing-off such tasks to techies.Equipped
with clear knowledge of Amiga's history, he is uniquely qualified to serve
it's future. A co-founder and past president of the Amiga Atlanta user
group, Joe has been continually active in Amiga hardware development since
1985. Before joining Amiga, Inc., he was an Engineer at Scientific-Atlanta,
a leading IT product developer and producer. His diverse experience also
includes R&D Engineering at BellSouth Telecommunications,
 Colorgraphic Communications, and designing video games at Health-Science
Media. A professed "rocket scientist," in his pre-Amiga days, at the
Missile Systems Division of Rockwell International. Joe Torre has been a
champion motorcycle roadracer; today he continues as an acknowledged
champion of Amiga.

Dr. Allan Havemose, Software Development

Dr. Havemose received his Master of Science Degree and Ph.D. from the
Mathematical Institute, Technical University of Denmark. Dr. Havemose's
Amiga experience includes founding a company called COMPAL; Amiga Technical
Support Manager for Commodore ESCO in Frankfurt, Germany; and Manager of
Amiga software development for Commodore International Services
Corporation. In 1994 he joined the Digital Sound Corporation as Vice
President of Engineering. 1996 saw Dr. Havemose at ARK Logic (an ICS
Company). He was hired as President and CEO to turn around the struggling
computer-graphics company. In 1997 he moved up to ICS's corporate office as
Vice President of Strategic Planning. In 1998 Dr. Havemose founded the
company Viking Analytics. Viking Analytics is a research and development
company

for computer trading models for currency, stock, and commodity markets. Dr.
Havemose shares the 1991 IEEE Information Theory Society Prize Paper Award
with J. Justesen, K. Larsen, T. Hoholdt, and H.E.Jensen. He also holds the
patent for cross-interleaved error correcting encoded data. Currently Dr.
Havemose enjoys the sun of California while living in San Jose.

Kelli Newby, Administrative Assistant/Bookkeeper

Kelli Newby joined Amiga, Inc. in September '97 as the
bookkeeper/Administrative Assistant. She has 11 years experience in the
