@node "gr1" "Blob"

@{fg shine} Blob@{fg text}

 From the moment you load Blob you can tell your on to a winner, there is 
no fancy intro sequence, just a straight forward menu, but some how the 
author makes it look so good. You have a variety of options and then you go
onto the player selection screen. At this point find as many people as you 
can, get the family together, call your neighbours and friends round, and 
when you have 8 players plug in your 2-way joystick adaptor and click on 
go! [-ed but i thought you had no friends lee :)]

 Actually I was telling a lie, you don`t need 8 players, or a 2-way 
joystick adaptor to play this game, but the more players the better, if 
you have two players it is not that good and you can`t really get a 
playable game in. Three players is really the minimum, and if your 
wondering about a one player option, you can`t have one, you actually need 
friends to play this!

 When you eventually get into the game the first level loads which, I 
assume, is called "Yikes! Clouds!". All the players Blobs will now fall 
down from the sky, a while later when the 4 players huddled around the 
keyboard realise what colour they are you can start to play. The idea is 
to jump on one of the other Blobs, which in turn are trying to jump on you,
this is why you need quite a few players, when two of you are playing it is
really hard to jump on each other, and once on of the blobs is dead you 
can`t go for another one.

 If you have a few players playing at one time you could get bonus' by 
getting 3-in-a-row or a pant dropping 10-in-a-row`s, both acompanied with 
there own sounds. However, this is much harder in a team game because when 
you jump on your own player you`ve lost your only chance!

 Another great thing about this game is the sounds, you have to hear them 
to get the feel. The music is great too.

 As this is the shareware demo version of the game, you are limited to only
four levels of play, which are all really good and have their own good and 
bad points, the cost of the full game is 5 english pounds, a bit over 
priced if you ask me, you can get hold of commercial games for 2.25p if you
know where to look.

 All my friends really like this, and I would go as far to say, this is the
best P.D game ever, and i`m sure my friends would agree. All that is 
missing from this game is a decent one player option in which you can 
select as many computer players as you want. Oh well, can`t have 
everything, or can I?

