@node "gr3" "A3dSim"

@{fg shine} ModelSim@{fg text}

 ModelSim is not really a game as there is nothing to do. "Whats the point 
of making a game where you don`t do anything?", I hear you ask, well, the 
game is just an extra in the archive. The point of this is to demonstrate 
how to use AMOS 3D to create a flight simulator, and having a brief look at
the source code which is included, it looks very hard to programme, but 
don`t worry, because there are loads of REM`s about!

 Well, the idea here, is to control a model plane around some landscape, 
thats it, its quite hard at first, but when you get used to the controls 
you`ll have that rush of speed which makes this simply brilliant.

 When you first boot up this game you are presented witha dull text-based 
title screen telling you the controls, once disk activity stops it tells 
you to press any key to play, doing that, you get to the playing screen, 
in front of you there is the background scenary which is quite good, its a 
bit dull, but it really adds to the `feel' of the game.
                                                                  .___.
 To control the power you must press on of the number keys or the | _ |
key, its best to just press the 0 key, as that is quite a nice    | - |
speed, although it is harder to control than, say 4, it lets you  +---+
get some speed up and perform some great stunts in the air.

 As I think its brilliant, I took it down to my friends to show him that 
there is still life in his Amiga, I showed him briefly how to move, and he 
thought it was crap, but when he had a go, he changed his mind instantly.

 This is a great game, its best to play it when your own your own, because 
when your friends are round they`ll fall asleep watching you.

