@node "gr4" "Phaser Blast"

@{fg shine} Phaser Blast@{fg text}

 Phaser Blast is a remake of the Atari Classic Laser Blast. The idea is to 
destroy the tanks below before they destroy you, and it is easy.

 The graphics in this game are by far the worst i`ve seen, the tanks which 
roam about at the bottom of the screen don`t look a bit like tanks! But 
they say graphics are not the most important part of the game; the most 
important part is gameplay, but there isn`t much of that either!

 You`ve most proberly guessed that I hate this game, by now, but dispite 
that fact i`m really quite good at it (me showing off again). At the 
start of the game you get 3 space ship things which you can move about in 
an area about half the screen in size. Every now and again tanks come 
along and the idea is to fire your blue beam at them so they blow up and 
you get 30 points, sounds easy? Well, yes it is, but the tanks fire their 
red beams at you! They hardly ever fire straight up at you so look out!

 Every 1000 points you get you are rewarded with an extra ship/life, 
whatever, you don`t really need that many lives as you rarely die! 

 After you have played your first game you have the option to play again, 
if you are stupid enough to press Y then you`ll start another game, but this 
time you start with your previous score and you gain a few lives depending 
on how many points you got. Maybe a bug there Mr. Author????

 I hate this game, personally I think it is crap and it hasn`t been thought
through that well, but at least it is better than a number guessing game. 
If you were stupid enough to buy an Atari and actually liked this game you 
might want to get this, but if not, don`t waste your time!

