@node "ur1" "Amigaload"

@{fg shine} Amigaload@{fg text}
 
 Amigaload is a program to display various things like your cpu power
and how much chip, fast mem you have left on an attractive looking wb
window. It has four meters for CPUload, Ready, Fast and Chip. Fast and
Chip are meters to show you how much memory you have left. CPUload is
to show how much of your CPU power is being used at that time, so if you
are running many applications then you will find that the meter is 
further over than if you were running less. I don't really know what
'Ready' does as i've scoured the whole document but can't find anything
relating to this but it obviously must be something useful!

 One of the best features of Amigaload is that you can connect up a
small circuit which plugs into the mouse/joystick ports and can have
real life flashing LEDs and LCD displays insted of the wb version,
of course you'd have to build the circuit but diagrams are supplied
so it shouldn't be to hard for you people who like to have a tinker with
the hardware.

 Overall a nice simple program that can do more than meets the eye, if
your interested in how much cpu is being used by various programs make
sure you download this either from aminet or www.hgs.se/~tl94hfl/

