@node "ur3" "c00ltext"

@{fg shine} c00ltext@{fg text}

 If you've ever seen writting where one letter is up and the next is
down and they continue on like this then you'll know what i'm on about.
This program does exactly that. It takes your normal text file and 
converts it into up and down text with other funny charictors thrown
in here and there. Its quite a good program but I can't see any real
use for it, why would you want your letters up and down so it makes
text harder to read? The main problem is there is no interface so you
have to use commands after running the program in a cli. This is not
the best possible way for this program as you need about 5 different
commands and if you get one wrong you've got to re-do the whole thing.

 Overall this gets the job done well but there isn't much point to
this type of program is there? if you need to do weird text or just
want your documents to look funny get this, otherwise you'd have no
real use for it.

